Patch for building GNU binutils 2.8.1 on modern Linux (glibc 2.9+, GCC 4+).
Binutils 2.8.1 (1998) is the default for Linux 2.0 libc5 cross-compilers.
This version is close to 2.9 and generally builds cleanly with fewer patches.

Issues addressed:
  1. libiberty/getline.c: POSIX getline() conflict
  2. libiberty/strsignal.c: sys_siglist const declaration
  3. gas/app.c: strsignal prototype conflict
  4. configure.in / configure: missing HAVE_* for modern glibc
  5. Makefile.in: -Werror in some subdirectory Makefiles

Apply with: patch -p1 -d binutils-2.8.1 < binutils-2.8.1-modern-linux.patch

--- a/libiberty/getline.c
+++ b/libiberty/getline.c
@@ -1,7 +1,9 @@
 /* Replacement for getline. */
+#define getline libiberty_getline
+
 #include <stdio.h>
 int
-getline (lineptr, n, stream)
+libiberty_getline (lineptr, n, stream)
      char **lineptr;
      size_t *n;
      FILE *stream;
--- a/libiberty/strsignal.c
+++ b/libiberty/strsignal.c
@@ -1,4 +1,8 @@
 /* Extended support for using signal names. */
+#define _GNU_SOURCE 1
 #include <stdio.h>
 #include <signal.h>
-extern char *sys_siglist[];
+#ifndef sys_siglist
+extern const char * const sys_siglist[];
+#endif
+
--- a/gas/app.c
+++ b/gas/app.c
@@ -30,2 +30,2 @@
-extern char *strsignal ();
+/* strsignal is in <string.h> on modern glibc; don't re-declare */
 
